    <text>
        <body>
            <div frus:doc-dateTime-max="1937-09-12T19:00:00-05:00"
                frus:doc-dateTime-min="1937-09-12T19:00:00-05:00" n="586"
                subtype="historical-document" type="document" xml:id="d586">
                <note rend="inline" type="source">793.94/10039: Telegram</note>
                <head>
                    <hi rend="italic">The Ambassador in China</hi> (<persName type="from">
                        <hi rend="italic">Johnson</hi>
                    </persName>) <hi rend="italic">to the <gloss type="to">Secretary of
                            State</gloss>
                    </hi>
                </head>
                <opener>
                    <dateline rendition="#right">
                        <placeName>
                            <hi rend="smallcaps">Nanking</hi>
                        </placeName>, <date calendar="gregorian" when="1937-09-13T08:00:00+08:00"
                            >September 13, 1937—8 a.m.</date>
                        <lb/>[Received 8:32 a.m.]</dateline>
                </opener>
                <p>644. Official sources confirm press reports from Sian that Military Affairs
                    Commission has appointed Chu Teh, Commander and Peng Teh Hui, Vice Commander of
                    the Chinese Communist forces in the northwest which have been reorganized into
                    Government forces as the Eighth Route Army. According to official sources the
                    cooperation of these forces with Government forces in present hostilities can
                    not be described as formation of “popular front” because the Communists have
                    submerged themselves in that they have promised not to engage in Communist
                    propaganda, have relinquished the class struggle, have no longer their Communist
                    character and Chu Teh and Peng have sworn their allegiance and obedience to
                    Chiang Kai-shek.</p>
                <p>Sent to Department. Repeated to Peiping. By mail to Shanghai, Hankow. Peiping
                    mail Tientsin.</p>
                <closer>
                    <signed>
                        <hi rend="smallcaps">Johnson</hi>
                    </signed>
                </closer>
            </div>
        </body>
    </text>
